The Kebbi State government has taken proactive measures against the escalation of the coronavirus pandemic in the state. It has directed the closure of all public and private schools in the state for one month. Briefing the newsmen in Birnin Kebbi, the commissioner of Heath, Hon. Jafaar Mohammed, explained that though the state has not recorded any case of the virus, the state government through the Committee on Emergency Preparedness and Response, has taken series of measures to prevent the spread of the virus in the state. Some of the measures he added includes; screening of all travelers coming into the state through air and land borders this with aid of Port Health Division of the Federal Ministry of Heath; setting up of isolation camp for quarantine of all suspected cases identified through surveillance system which has intensified at all levels. Hon Jafaar therefore implored people in the state to support the government in achieving this objective and to remain calm and focused as well as cooperate with health officials. The commissioner, however, warned against spreading rumours about the disease and also advised them to always seek for information from the appropriate authority concerning the virus.